---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <main
    class="p-6 space-y-8 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 min-h-screen transition-colors"
  >
    <header class="text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Retos Frontend</h1>
    </header>

    <section>
      <header class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">DailyUI</h2>
      </header>
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">DailyUI #001</h3>
          <p>
            <span class="font-semibold">Prompt:</span> Sign Up
            <br />
            Create a sign up page, modal, form, or app screen related to signing
            up for something. It could be for a volunteer event, contest registration,
            a giveaway, or anything you can image.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/dailyui-001"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página de registro"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">DailyUI #002</h3>
          <p>
            <span class="font-semibold">Prompt:</span> Credit Card Checkout
            <br />
            Design a credit card checkout form or page. Don't forget the important
            elements such as the numbers, dates, security numbers, etc.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/dailyui-002"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página de registro"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">DailyUI #003</h3>
          <p>
            <span class="font-semibold">Prompt:</span> lorem
            <br />
            Lorem ipsum, dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Eos vero voluptates
            voluptate deserunt quasi, obcaecati quidem explicabo ea perferendis praesentium
            recusandae aliquam impedit deleniti reprehenderit facilis nihil labore
            voluptatum modi?
          </p>
          <a
            href="/dailyui-003"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página de registro"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section>
      <header class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Frontend Mentor</h2>
      </header>
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium flex items-center">
            Mortgage repayment calculator <span
              class="inline-block bg-green-200 dark:bg-green-700 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 text-sm px-2 py-1 rounded ml-3"
            >
              Junior
            </span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            This mortgage calculator is an excellent project for practicing
            working with forms, client-side validation, and updating the DOM.
            Remember to focus on accessibility, too!
          </p>
          <a
            href="/ticket-generator"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página del generador de tickets"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium flex items-center">
            Conference ticket generator <span
              class="inline-block bg-green-200 dark:bg-green-700 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 text-sm px-2 py-1 rounded ml-3"
            >
              Junior
            </span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            In this challenge, you'll create a form that generates a ticket.
            There's a lot of scope for customizing the generated ticket and
            putting your own stamp on the project.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/ticket-generator"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página del generador de tickets"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
        <article
          class="space-y-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors"
        >
          <h3 class="text-xl font-medium flex items-center">
            Bento grid
            <span
              class="inline-block bg-green-200 dark:bg-green-700 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 text-sm px-2 py-1 rounded ml-3"
            >
              Junior
            </span>
          </h3>
          <p>
            This challenge is perfect for testing your CSS Grid and responsive
            skills with this bento grid layout.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/ticket-generator"
            class="block text-center bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-colors"
            aria-label="Ir a la página del generador de tickets"
          >
            Ir a página
          </a>
        </article>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
